<br>
Forna was so lost, that's what happens when you get a mystery note from your father calling you away from your friends. She sighed, but no one caught on, because Bren was talking to Yavi. As Bren's words laced their way to her ears, inside she smiled. Quellious, her deity, her life support. Peace and Tranquility. It was what fueled her sanity, her life. <br>
<br>
As Forna followed the conversation, she grew even more lost. How could Bren think Yavi or even the furry one would harm any one? Her crystal blue eyes, watched him as he spoke. She yearned to talk with him, to confide in him, but now was nor the time nor the place. Maybe he would fill her in on this whole mess, then she could fill him in on the shattered mess of thoughts in her own mind. Outside she may have looked together, but inside... she was at war. <br>
<br>
Forna's sleek blonde hair whipped gently about, as a small breeze began to wind its way through the trees. The cool rush felt like water running over her skin, but the small bit of clarity she was feeling was smashed as Yavi began to speak. Could they not just move on! By Quellious, she wished peace upon them! She was all about the suggestion to eat earlier. Batwing Crunchies sounded so good right then...<br>
<br>
As Yavi rambled on about power, inside anger furrowed, 'I'll show you power,' she thought. It was one thing she hated. Boasting. Too bad she had nothing against the guy, 'til he started to boast. Could he not just open up to the gang! We were all so fun-loving, caring, and we were serious when need be. <br>
<br>
Forna's mouth opened to speak, but Paren jumped in. He, like her, wished this conversation to continue naught the way it was headed. She smiled as his words rang in her ears, they were beautiful...<br>
<br>
When Paren's little schpeel came to a close, she smiled at Bren, then looked back to Paren, &quot;Now, Paren, Hun, if you could only make your lyrics make that much sense!&quot; Smiling she looked to the group as a whole, &quot;What's said is done, shall we move on? I just came back from absence and I'm greeted by a petty spat. I don't know you at all, but I say we all make our way to town! We could hit the Tavren, have a round or two? Then, maybe even grab a bite to eat, yes?&quot; Her tummy rumbled at the thought. She chuckled, &quot;My stomach agrees, and we can all mingle while we're there, we can learn about furry there, Yavi and Amy? Hmmm? Whatcha say?&quot; Forna's eyes looked around, then right to Bren, they looked right into his, and she hope she got her message of distress across. She really wanted to talk, but she wanted to talk alone, with him.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/bfantasystoriesforum.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ryvian>Ryvian</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Warlord of Delnor</span><br>  Posts: 199<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/17/02 4:54 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/ffantasystoriesforumfrm7.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=12.topic&index=47>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: haha ahaha A bird hahaha wait... whoops</span><hr size=1> &quot;Forna have I told you that i love ya today yet? haha I also agree with that, guys we've just been done with a fight, and I'm starving starving starving!!! Let's go.&quot; Paren shot a glance over to Hoku who was silent this whole time, she had something on her mind and Paren was uncertain just what it was, maybe he'd get it out of her later, he'd have to sing a special song for truth. Thinking about that again, he decided that a song would be a bad idea seeing how she always took his songs the wrong way. So instead he