With mountains in the northern reach<br>
A band of travelers on their way<br>
On a quest, road hard for each<br>
It comes down to one which has to pay.<br>
<br>
While they fight, one will heal.<br>
Lightning will find each down their own trail<br>
And one with steel will prevail<br>
The one of song will bring bring down hail.<br>
<br>
Once the city of glory is reached<br>
A healer's song will be the end<br>
The blade will fail and heart will be breached<br>
A lone force it must defend.<br>
<br>
But now my friends the tale is heard<br>
It will not end here and you will send<br>
A song on the wind, one with a bird<br>
The song is done, but this is not the end.<br>
<br>
Looking up, Paren did not know what the words meant, he hardly did when he searched for a song in his skill. They came to him like cows to feed. Hoping that he had given them all a reminder that he truely could sing, Paren sighed and looked up to see a spot of the midday sky.  <br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/bfantasystoriesforum.showUserPublicProfile?gid=bonaki>Bonaki</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 9<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/18/02 4:10 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/ffantasystoriesforumfrm7.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=12.topic&index=53>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> A break in the night</span><hr size=1> The song actually was very nice and it helped to make the walk seem to go faster. He wondered if there was a bit of selo's mixed into the rythem. He smiled as Amy held on to his arm in the relaxed pace. The light at first didn't even make him think twice, he smiled though at the thought, sun light in this forest was a nice thing. Noting that everyone else had kept moving, but the bard had stopped. Yavi turned around. He looked as the bard stood in the sunlight stareing straight upwards at the sky. His arms were outstretched and the smile on his face said everything. Yavi felt Amy at his side cling closer and give him a hig. &quot;It's beautiful.&quot; she whispered to him. Yavi's smile grew, &quot;If you want to I'm sure he wouldn't mind you joining. I know how much the sky means to your people.&quot; Almost laughing at the smile that almost reached her finely pointed ears, Yavi let her go.<br>
<br>
Running almost to the bard who was softly humming the tune that all elves knew to sing to the sun. Stopping before him Amy timidly looked up at his face. The bard was taller than most elves, which is what gave his hybred lineage away. &quot;Do you mind if I join you?&quot; She asked softly not wanting to break his reverence. Without a word Paren's smile grew and he slightly nodded. Looking up to the sky, Amy slowly stepped into the light. The warmth! that was the first thing she felt, her smile only grew as her arms spread. Her and the bard begun the dance and the two twirled and embraced each other as brother and sister of the sky. <br>
<br>
Yavi smiled as well seeing Amy in such bliss was something that nearly brought a tear to his eye. It had been months since she were this happy. He nearly broke his stoic resolve when she began to sing the words to the bard's tune. In elvish, Yavi could not understand, but a few things. At first when he had seen Amy sing to the sky before, he had been somewhat upset that he couldn't understand it. He had asked why she couldn't sing it in common so he could hear it too, but she had laughed and told him it was a prayer and what he could not understand really did not have words in the common tongue. Realizing that it was horribly rude to ask for a translation to a sacred prayer, Yavi had apologized right away. Looking at the two, he nearly felt as if he was no longer needed. *Maybe I'm not* he thought, maybe the blade wasn't as good as a guard anymore.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/bfantasystoriesforum.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ryvian>Ryvian</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Warlord of Delnor</span><br>  Posts: 202<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/18/02 4:35 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/ffantasystoriesforumfrm7.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=12.topic&index=54>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> wow dude nice</span><hr size=1> not careing where he was or who this was next to him, Paren was too absorbed in the moment. The song was perfect and the sunlight was not abridged by any clouds. This moment was perfect. He hadn't cared if the other's had kept going, infact he hoped they would. He didn't think that they would understand. After all Bren was euridite, and none of the others had even a small bit of elvish, atleast he was fairly sure. Again he smiled, but then his thoughts began to return to him. This was not the spot of the hole in the forest... maybe a tree had fallen, but wouldn't he see the stump or even the tree? Confused, but not even careing anymore, Paren kept his tune and spun the small elf girl in his arms. <br>
<br>
After the song had ended and the day's song to the sun was finished, Paren looked up at the sky. &quot;I wish I could stand in this light forever, but Amy, you look hungry.&quot; The smile on her face told him everything. &quot;Ok, let's go.&quot; he said helping her up.<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :rolleyes --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/eyes.gif ALT=":rolleyes"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/bfantasystoriesforum.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zulik>zulik</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Angel of Death</span><br>  Posts: 384<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/18/02 5:35 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/ffantasystoriesforumfrm7.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=12.topic&index=55>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: okies here we go</span><hr size=1> ( sorry i was down for like 5 days im gonna make it up! and i love you all!)<br>
