</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/bfantasystoriesforum.showUserPublicProfile?gid=bonaki>Bonaki</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 10<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/18/02 7:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/ffantasystoriesforumfrm7.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=12.topic&index=56>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> sunlight</span><hr size=1> Even though they had left the small circle of sunlight, Amy's eyes still shone with the light. She grasped tightly on his arm as the bard played softly on his flute the jig of vigor. It appeared to Yavi the only thing keeping the two young ones on their feet. Glancing up ahead, he could not see the others. Paren had told them that they had probably just gone ahead to the city. He knew that Forna would want to eat more than any of them, and Bren needed some sleep. Yavi nodded and so simply followed the bard. There seemed to be things in the darkness following them, but the bard noted that they should pay them no attention. Paren had explained to Yavi and Amy that those were skeleton heritics that roamed and scouted, but hardly ever attacked unless attacked first. Yavi tried hard to keep his hand from the hilt of his blade. Growing wrapped up in his thoughts, Yavi let go of Amy's hand but kept walking. His eyes glazed over and his attention that was always alert grew sluggish. Soon he had found he was completely lost and did not know where he was. He looked to find Amy but found no one, not even the noise of the two walking. Panic coursed through him as he tried to remember just how long ago he had lost sight of them. His hand went for the hilt of his sword when swords from the blackness leveled on him. &quot;Drop your sword.&quot; came the demand. Peering into the darkness Yavi saw sets of red glowing eyes shine at him.<br>
<br>
Amy was now attached to Paren's arm. He told her he knew where they were going even though the forest was growing darker, if that was even possible. Feeling so comfortable with the bard, she did not even notice Yavi's absence. With her arm hooked with Paren's and her head resting on his shoulder, the two walked in companionable silence. <br>
<br>
&quot;Who are you!&quot; Yavi shouted. &quot;Where are you taking me!&quot; Kicking at the skeleton, he was smacked hard with the butt of a spear. &quot;Shut up fleshie. If you do not be quiet I will feed you to the hole!&quot; Yavi did not know what that meant and rubbed his jaw where he had been struck. &quot;Is that where I think it is!&quot; Feeling instantly foolish Yavi had wished he did not make such an aggressive impression on the cleric and his friends. &quot;I want you to know, that you will feel my steel before I die.&quot; The skeleton smiled, &quot;Not likely. If you could reanimate my flesh maybe, but you are no magician.&quot; Spitting at the bones walking, Yavi wished that Amy had found a good guardian in Paren, as they reached gates of Paineel.<br>
<br>
Reaching the gates of the city, Paren smiled at Amy. &quot;And we're here.&quot; Wrapping an arm around her shoulders pulling her closer, &quot;Now lets get you something to eat.&quot; Amy smiled and nodded. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/bfantasystoriesforum.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zulik>zulik</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Angel of Death</span><br>  Posts: 385<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/19/02 8:18 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/ffantasystoriesforumfrm7.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=12.topic&index=57>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: okies here we go</span><hr size=1> ( I will play two people! the Kerran and rill's brother)<br>
